\n<Constance>Radlo's mom is such a great cook! She praises me a lot if I
finish my meal, but I can't leave any even if I wanted
to—it's too delicious!

\n<Constance>But then, Samuel starts teasing me saying, "You'll get fat,"
and it always turns into a fight. I don't even want to
fight!
\n<Aventus>...

\n<Samuel>Dig dig dig... If I dig a hole here, some really gross bugs
come out. I'll show them to you when they do.

\n<Fair>I'm the eldest here! That means I'm the most important!
Second only to Lady Radlo! Show some respect!

\n<Fair>Ah, but I read in a book that important people don't say
they're important themselves! I'm not saying I'm important,
but I am the eldest! I'm really not important! It's true!
\n<Francois>You know, I actually think that Radlo's mom is pretty cute!

\n<Francois>Hey, this is a secret, alright? Don't you dare tell anyone
else! If you do, I'll pinch you!

\n<Rui>"I want to become a scholar. If I can solve even one of the
10,000 mysteries of this world, then it's a victory for me!"

\n<Rui>"Some people say this place isn't suited for studying, but
I'm sure there are things that can only be learned here.
I'll show them that one's birth and upbringing have nothing
to do with scholarship!"

\n<Old Man>"Staying in the noble district means a lot of climbing up
and down, which is quite harsh on an old body like mine."

\n<Old Man>"The head of the house is furious. If it's discovered that
I've been turning a blind eye like this, I might lose my
head. Please persuade them if that happens."

\n<Old Man>"Right now, everyone in the mansion is searching for the two
of you. Well, they'd never imagine you're in Dri-Ne, so
there's no worry of being found."

\n<Old Man>"How did I know you were here? Well, as your educator, I can
see right through both of your thoughts."

\n<Old Man>"However, my body can't keep up anymore... It took quite
some time to get here. It was about six days of rest and
travel by carriage."

\n<Old Man>"You didn't come all this way in one night, did you? No
matter how high your physical abilities and the blessings of
the wind are... Goodness. You're practically a monster."

\n<Old Man>"It seems beastfolk are rare around here. I've only seen an
elderly tanuki. I'm an old dog myself."

\n<Old Man>"I should have dressed more shabbily. The residents of the
slums are giving me quite the look."

\n<Old Man>"I'm well-versed in self-defense, so there's no problem if
I'm attacked. Still spry in my old age. Just a bit of joint
pain, though."

\n<Old Man>"I won't enter the Adventurers' Guild. It would be
troublesome if your identities were questioned. I'll just
loiter around here."

\n<Old Man>"That vase was a gift from the head of the house two
generations ago. We were close in age, and he treated me
like a friend... He was a bright person, like Miss Chelsea."

\n<Old Man>"The fact that it was broken by you might have been some
sort of divine revelation. I take it as a message from two
generations ago."

\n<Old Man>"You use 'Cat's Paw' in combat, but it was originally meant
to assist with writing documents and such. It's a magic used
by the executive branch."

\n<Old Man>"There's a saying, 'even a cat's hand is desired,' right?
That's the origin of this phrase. It's that venerable a
magic."

\n<Old Man>"I am watching over both of your growths. However, since you
left home on your own, I will not lend a hand. My hands,
that is."

\n<Old Man>"By the way... You are still in the midst of growing up. I
hope you make the right choices.\C[1] (Current Karma Value
0)"

\n<Old Man>"By the way... You seem to have grown since before you came
here. This old man is a bit relieved.\C[1] (Current Karma
Value \v[270])"

\n<Old Man>"By the way... You seem to have changed your aura. Don't do
anything too reckless.\C[14] (Current Karma Value \v[270])"

\n<Lintei>Ugh...! I'm weak against these sudden attacks! I'm the type
who needs to prepare thoroughly!

\n<Lintei>But I can't afford to lose! Lynx, Cunes... lend me your
strength...!

\n<Female>The name of this town is "Drain". It means sinkhole. It's a
hole that suddenly appeared due to the ground collapsing.
This town was built inside of it.

\n<Female>The upper class lives above this town, and people like us,
the lower class, live off the scraps they throw away.

\n<Female>This is where those who have lost their way end up,
swallowed up like into a drain. All sorts of schemes and
desires swirl around here.
\n<Dirty Dog>*pant*...*pant*...*pant*...

\n<Annie>Rui! The town is in chaos! We've evacuated everyone who
can't fight! But there are monsters in the residential area
too...! Damn it! Why is this happening all of a sudden!!

\n<Dodon>Damn it! What the hell is this all of a sudden!! Hey! Rui!
It's an attack! Kill the monsters!!

\n<Dodon>Ahh!? Rui!? Not looking, huh! Maybe they're fighting
somewhere else! You protect the town too!

\n<Dodon>Ahh!? Ones!? Not looking, huh! Maybe they're fighting
somewhere else! You protect the town too!
\n<Rakura>Tch! Take this! Lightning Spear!
\n<Rakura>Why won't you die already! You monster...!

\n<Innkeeper>"What's this? Monsters are attacking? Is this how the town
ends? Pathetic."

\n<Innkeeper>"Huh? One of the twins? I don't know. I might have seen
them, but I don't remember now. How many beers do you think
I've had?"

What a hassle this has become. You're going to fight, aren't
you? Huh.

\n<Peddler>Money? Of course, I'm taking it. I'm a merchant till I die.

\n<Tanuki Beastman>I got caught living it up after transforming leaves into

cell, right? They say home is where you make it.

\n<Tanuki Beastman>Hm? Ah, a cat beastperson. I was just looking for something
edible.

\n<Tanuki Beastman>The little ones at the orphanage are in a pickle, I need to
teach them which bugs can be eaten and which can't.

parameters: \n<Demon Lord'S Aide>"Eh-... Welcome to the Demon Lord's castle, humans."
\n<Old Man>"Wha, Demon Lord's castle...!? What do you mean!?"

\n<Siebel>"Eh...? It's just a forest. There's just a chair placed in
the forest. Eh? Demon Lord?"
1テラ困惑
\n<Terra>"Um... Demon Lord? What exactly is this..."

\n<Demon Lord>"You know... you all were about to be buried alive. Do you
get that... ugh... I feel sick..."

\n<Demon Lord'S Aide>"By the Demon Lord's ingenious arrangement, you were all
invited to the Demon Lord's castle via a wide-range
teleport. Isn't that right?"

\n<Demon Lord>"No, that's not it... Look, you wouldn't understand... ha...
ha..."

\n<Demon Lord>"To me, demons are like... umm. Bottle ships. You get it? Do
you know what a bottle ship is?"

\n<Demon Lord>"You use toothpicks, tweezers, and stuff to make intricate
ship models inside a bottle. That's what I'm talking about.
Cough!"

\n<Demon Lord>"They're like works of art. Super delicate. Especially the
higher-ups. Well, imps and such are fine even if they get
crushed."

\n<Demon Lord>"Every single day, gluing tiny parts together, meticulously,
meticulously, inserting tweezers into the bottle, and if
even one part is wrong, it's all over."

\n<Demon Lord>"It's madness, isn't it? And when it's finally complete.
Have you ever thought about how it feels to have it
destroyed?"

\n<Demon Lord>"It's beyond just flipping out. To me, demons are bottle
ships. How about that. Did I make myself clear? Ugh, I feel
like vomiting..."

\n<Aide>"As expected, your analogy is very easy to understand. Even
the dim-witted war bears would have grasped it."
1テラ困惑

\n<Terra>"So, in other words... you teleported us over a wide area to
save us, and humans came along too, is that correct?"

\n<Demon Lord>"I only knew the approximate location. Thanks to that, I've
been feeling dizzy and nauseous since... cough! I'm drained
of magic power."

\n<Demon Lord>"Wait a minute... let me rest. Don't you all move... cough!
cough!"

\n<Ladro>"(The stronghold of demons...? But for now, it's good that
the children are safe. We're not out of danger yet
though...)"
1シスター困惑

\n<Soel>"(Teleporting this many from a distance...? It must have

\n<Bijou>"(I only remember up until the guild was blown away. If I
knew this would happen, I should have escaped sooner... My
drunkenness has completely worn off.)"

\n<Guild Master>"(That's the Demon Lord? Damn it. Can't see from here. Quite
the talkative one.)"

\n<Old Man>"(The young master and young lady seem safe as well... But
why are they on that side...?)"
\n<Demon Lord>"Phew... I'm starting to feel a bit better. It's tough..."

\n<Demon Lord>"So, what I'm trying to say is this. What's done is done.
Humans. You're all going to be killed."

\n<Demon Lord>"But that's not a constructive conversation. Rather, it's
not interesting. This must be some kind of fate."

\n<Demon Lord>"Humans are ugly creatures. You're humans yet you were
almost killed by humans. Judging from the coagulation
crystal matter, it was planned from the start."

\n<Demon Lord>"Using the coagulation crystal to lure demons and attack the
slums. Then burying everyone alive to catch them all in one
fell swoop. Anyone here have an idea who might be
responsible?"

\n<Guild Master>"Ah... Yeah, no doubt about it. What the Demon Lord is
saying is correct. It was orchestrated by Count Noblesse."
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>"...(It's my fault for stealing it. Even if I was forced to
steal, it's... my fault that everyone got involved.)"
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>"...(It's my fault for stealing it. Even if I was forced to
steal, it's... my fault that everyone got involved.)"

\n<Demon Lord>"Such a plan couldn't have been concocted overnight. There
must have been meticulous preparation. Gunpowder, sorcerers,
barrier technicians. Could they have conveniently gathered
in such a short time?"

\n<Demon Lord>"If things had stayed the same, you all would have been
buried alive by those above. In other words, I'm your
lifesaver. Right?"

\n<Demon Lord>"Your lives were picked up by me. It's only logical to use
them for me. You were about to be killed by humans. Become
my subordinates and let's take revenge on the humans."

\n<Dodon>"True... Unforgivable. They tried to kill us... all the
people in the slums."

\n<Siebel>"We were certainly a thorn in their side. Or rather, under
their eye. But being buried alive... that's too much."

\n<Innkeeper Granny>"Those scumbags above. They even tried to bury this old
lady. They could at least wait until I die."
\n<Guild Master>"I'm boiling with rage. That bastard..."

\n<Lintei>"No! If the demons hadn't attacked, those above wouldn't
have done such a thing!"

\n<Lintei>"You mustn't listen to what the Demon Lord says! We are
humans! Humans shouldn't harbor hatred towards each other!
Demons are meant to lead people astray..."
\n<Rakura>"Lintei!!"

\n<Demon Lord>"Don't get the choices mixed up. I'm not talking about
siding with humans or demons. It's about whether you become
my subordinates or die right now."
\n<Lintei>"It's... okay. It's not a... fatal wound..."

\n<Aide>"No, it's definitely a fatal wound. Your guts are spilling
out."

\n<Annie>"Okay, I understand! We'll do as you say! But please heal
Lintei! I beg you!"

\n<Demon Lord>"Fine. Well, that's acceptable. Always obey my orders. If
you do, I'll at least guarantee your lives."
1ラドロP真顔2

\n<Radro>"Please, Demon Lord-sama. I don't care what happens to me.
Could you please spare just the children?"

\n<Demon Lord>"I'm not talking about forgiving or not forgiving.
Seriously, humans don't listen. Fine! Whatever! It's so
annoying! Do as you like!"
1ラドロP照れ2

\n<Radro>"...(Ah, as soon as I felt relieved, suddenly my strength
is... I feel dizzy...)"

\n<Radro>"...(Rui...)"

\n<Bijou>"(I see. How interesting. If it means my life is saved, I
don't care which side I'm on.)"

\n<Demon Lord>"Hey! Demons! If you eat these guys without my permission,
I'll kill you! Got it? Those who try to escape can be
eaten!"

\n<Demon Lord>"For now, make these guys build a house or something. Keep a
close watch on them. That's all! Dismissed! Succubi, stay
behind!"
